Write functions for the controlled input of an integer and for calculating the factorial of an integer. The number should be within the interval [0, 10]. 
In case of unsuccessful input, the function should print "Invalid input" and request the value again until the user provides correct input.
Use the provided code skeleton for the solution, and ensure that the return type, function name (identifier), and parameter list of the functions adhere to the given requirements.

Tests:
InvalidInput_nan_test
• Inputs:
a
5
• Expected output: Invalid input (included)

InvalidInput_negativ_test
• Inputs:
-5
5
• Expected output: Invalid input (included)

InvalidInput_large_test
• Inputs:
20
5
• Expected output: Invalid input (included)

The test.c file contains CUnit tests:
Tested function Parameter Expected return value
factor 0 1
factor 5 120
